{
  "stem": "1858.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 241.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The old people or the very young-- by old I mean anyone over 35-- or young kids, like myself-- kids under 15 or so-- were rendered useless by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Therefore, the strong and young people were being constantly taken away, shipped to labor camps, the others to Auschwitz, unknown to us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were constantly told that we would be resettled to a different city since ours was overcrowded.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't know if we chose to believe that, or if we believed it because who could imagine that there is such a place as Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But what it did, it broke up the family unit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by breaking up the family unit, we each served as a hostage.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew that if we get out of line, my sisters could suffer, be killed for it, and they, in turn, felt the same thing.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So when today you are asked, why did you not fight back or-- although, there was, in every ghetto, in every concentration camp, there was an uprising of a sort, or sabotage there of a sort.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- such as like in our-- in our ghetto, there was formed organization, [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH]-- it was two brothers-- they started organizing an underground movement.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the two leaders were caught, shot, and they broke it up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But even if they wouldn't be caught, what were the weapons that we had to fight?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Without the outside help of the Polish underground, it was impossible to rise against the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Today, if you hear of wars or uprisings, you know that these people get weapons from somebody.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody in this world, this whole huge world, nobody helped us by supplying us with weapons.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
